Class SocketClientHandler

java.lang.Object
org.mio.progettoingsoft.network.server.socket.SocketClientHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
Runnable, Remote, VirtualClient
public class SocketClientHandler extends Object implements VirtualClient, Runnable
Handles communication with a single client connected via a Socket. This class acts as both a VirtualClient (allowing the server to send messages to the client) and a Runnable (for continuous message reception from the client).

  • Constructor Details

    • SocketClientHandler

      public SocketClientHandler(Socket socket, BlockingQueue<Message> receivedMessages) throws IOException
      Constructs a new SocketClientHandler. Initializes the socket, message queue, and sets up input/output streams for object communication.
      Parameters:
      socket - The client's Socket connection.
      receivedMessages - The BlockingQueue where incoming messages from this client will be put.
      Throws:
      IOException - If an I/O error occurs when creating the input/output streams.

  • Method Details

    • run

      public void run()
      The main execution loop for handling messages from a client. If an IOException or ClassNotFoundException occurs during message reading, it logs a "Client crashed" error and breaks the loop, effectively terminating the handler for this client.
      Specified by:
      run in interface Runnable
